name: Kick-off Meetup, Intro to Google Tech-stack & Android app development

venue.name: Sen. Richard C. and Dr. Annette N. Shelby Center for Engineering Technology

description:
Join our slack channel (GDG Cloud Auburn) - https://goo.gl/e2ezGZ
Follow our Facebook page - https://fb.com/GDGCloudAuburn

Agenda:

6:00--6:15: Socializing & Pizza (Thanks Auburn ACM & AUHacks organizers for food and drinks!)
6:15--6:30: Opening Session - Jay Patel
6:35--6:50: Introduction to Google Tech-stack - Andrew J. McGehee
7:00-7:30: How to get started with Android? - Nikolay Sargsyan
7:30-7:45: Q&A

Introduction to Google Tech-stack
Speaker : Andrew J. McGehee
Andrew talks about what we are looking for our 2019 GDG track and crazy tech from Google.

Introduction to Android dev
Speaker : Nikolay Sargsyan
Come along to learn how to get started with Android as we demonstrate building a small mobile application live on stage.

Abstract: Let's kick-off our first meetup with Google tech-stack and get started with Android app development. Nikolay demonstrate how to set up and configure workflows in Android Studio, builds a small demo, and talk about publishing app to play store.
